Aleph Package Manager
---------------------
Usage:
    %CMD% <subcommand> [options]

Subcommands:
    help, --help                              Shows this help message and exits.
    version, --version                        Shows version information.
    install, i <package1 package2 ...>        Installs the specified packages.
    remove, rm <package1 package2 ...>        Removes the specified packages.
    search, s <searchterm>                    Searches through the package database for *searchterm* (supports regex).
    list, l                                   Lists all packages inside the package database.

Examples:
    ./aleph install example-package1 example-package2
    ./aleph remove example-package1
    ./aleph search libexample
    ./aleph list

For detailed documentation, visit: <https://github.com/ico277/aleph>
